summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Western Sahara, particularly resolution 1108 (1997) and the President's statement of 19 March 1997,
Recalling resolution 1308 (2000) and the Convention on the Safety of UN and Associated Personnel,
Reaffirming Charter provisions,
Considering the Secretary-General's report of 20 June 2001,
Expressing support for the Personal Envoy and MINURSO's efforts to implement the Settlement Plan,
Takes note of the Polisario Front's Official Proposals, the draft Framework Agreement on the Status of Western Sahara, and the Memorandum of the Government of Algeria;

1. Decides to extend MINURSO's mandate until 30 November 2001;
2. Supports the Secretary-General's efforts to facilitate direct or proximity talks under the Personal Envoy's auspices to discuss the draft Framework Agreement and other proposals;
3. Affirms consideration of the Polisario Front's official proposals during ongoing discussions;
4. Recalls that nothing will be agreed until everything is agreed, and parties' negotiations will not prejudice their final positions;
5. Urges parties to solve the problem of people unaccounted for and abide by international humanitarian law;
6. Requests the Secretary-General to assess the situation and provide recommendations on MINURSO's future mandate and composition;
7. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
